        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 1:35PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 135 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of San Felipe, or 11 miles east of Bellville, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hempstead, Prairie View, Pine Island, and Monaville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM CDT for
southeastern Texas.</instruction>
